11/05/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The reputed mastermind of Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic's assassination appeared before Belgrade's Special Court on Monday (10 May). 
Milorad Lukovic, also known as "Legija", asked the judges for more time to prepare his defence. 
He was told to enter a plea on 10 June. 
Lukovic's lawyer said that his client would reveal everything he knows about March 2003 assassination. 
Lukovic is among 12 people on trial for the murder. 
(AP, BBC, CNN, AFP, B92, Tanjug - 10/05/04)
